  "prompt": "What is the best WYSIWYG editor for Drupal 7?",
  "response": "When it comes to selecting the best WYSIWYG editor for Drupal 7, several factors come into play, such as ease of use, feature set, compatibility, and community support. Based on these considerations, one of the most popular and highly recommended WYSIWYG editors for Drupal 7 is CKEditor.\n\n### Why CKEditor?\n\n1. **Wide Adoption and Support**: CKEditor is widely used and well-supported within the Drupal community. This means there are plenty of resources available for troubleshooting and customization.\n\n2. **Feature-Rich**: CKEditor comes with a comprehensive set of features, including text formatting, image handling, tables, and more. It\u2019s highly customizable, allowing you to tailor the toolbar and functionality to meet your specific needs.\n\n3. **Integration**: CKEditor integrates seamlessly with Drupal 7 through the WYSIWYG module or the CKEditor module. This makes it easy to set up and configure.\n\n4. **User-Friendly**: CKEditor is known for its user-friendly interface, which is beneficial for content editors who may not be technically savvy.\n\n### Steps to Install CKEditor in Drupal 7\n\n1. **Install the WYSIWYG Module**:\n   - Download the WYSIWYG module from Drupal.org.\n   - Enable the module through the Modules page in your Drupal administration panel.\n\n2. **Install CKEditor**:\n   - Download the CKEditor library from the official CKEditor website.\n   - Place the CKEditor library in the `sites/all/libraries` directory of your Drupal installation. The directory should be named `ckeditor`.\n\n3. **Configure the WYSIWYG Module**:\n   - Navigate to `admin/config/content/wysiwyg`.\n   - Select the content types and input formats where you want to use CKEditor.\n   - Choose CKEditor as the editor and configure the toolbar settings to your preference.\n\n4. **Testing**:\n   - After configuration, go to a node edit page to test the CKEditor functionality.\n\n### Alternative Options\n\nWhile CKEditor is highly recommended, other options like TinyMCE are also popular and worth considering depending on your specific needs:\n\n- **TinyMCE**: Another robust WYSIWYG editor with a strong feature set and good integration with Drupal 7 via the WYSIWYG module.\n\nUltimately, the \"best\" editor may vary based on your specific requirements and preferences. CKEditor, however, stands out for its balance of features, ease of use, and community support, making it an excellent choice for most Drupal 7 sites.",
